#compdef rage-mount
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream str4d/rage
# rage/src/bin/rage-mount/cli.rs clap-derive `AgeMountOptions`
# struct + `#[arg(...)]` macros. Unlike rage/rage-keygen (already
# covered in earlier rounds) which use clap_complete for completion
# generation, rage-mount has 2 positional + 5 flag arguments
# extracted source-direct from the clap struct definition
# (rage-mount's help text is internationalized via `fl!()` calls so
# the descriptions here are summarized from upstream behavior).
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# str4d rage-mount R136d — FUSE mount of an age-encrypted tar or
# zip archive as a read-only filesystem. Sister tool to `rage`
# (Rust impl of age encryption) and `rage-keygen` (key generator)
# which are already covered in the corpus.

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
  '(-V --version)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
  '(-t --types)'{-t+,--types=}'[archive type (tar or zip)]:type:(tar zip)' \
  '--max-work-factor=[max acceptable scrypt work factor (mitigates DoS on bad passphrases)]:WF:' \
  '*'{-i+,--identity=}'[identity file for decryption (repeatable for multiple keys)]:identity:_files' \
  '1:age-encrypted archive file:_files -g "*.(age|tar.age|zip.age)"' \
  '2:mountpoint directory:_directories'
